NIGERIAN rapper and hype man, Arinze Oruche aka AO-Machine is certain that the future of the rap game in Nigeria is exciting and however rap lovers can be optimistic it will get even bigger. The hypeman made this known to The Nation in a recent interview while speaking about what the future holds for the rap industry in Nigeria. He said, “Rap in Naija is not for the weak or the meek because the journey most likely will be longer and harder. But the future of rap in Nigeria is exciting because rappers are tapping into some of the sub-genres of rap (like Trap and Drill) that are more commercially appealing lately.”   Laolu Gbenjo set for one of kind US Tour     I don’t want to be a social media husband, says Stan Nze     I don’t see anything wrong with two adults recording…   AO-Machine, one of the few hypemen with songs to their credit, says he’s hopeful of what the future holds for him. “It makes me very versatile and hopeful because the hype-man industry in Nigeria is blowing up really fast so that means more opportunities for someone like me that is a master at both.” AO-Machine has two songs to his credit and they include ‘This one loud o’ featuring Dremo, The Flowolf, and Ike Onyema; and ‘Zuzu’ featuring DJ Emmbasse. - Advertisement - On the conceptualisation of his lyrics, he said, “I feel like a very relatable rapper, so you will see me put a lot of things or words used in everyday conversation and since my background is that of both Naija and the United States of America, I try to bring both sides updated on slangs and lifestyles through the music. ‘this one loud oh’ is simply an expression used when something shocks you or is too much to handle/digest.” SPONSORED